# Missing Test Case Creation Rules

When missing scenarios are found, either create the test cases through Qase MCP or provide Qase-ready cases.

Create or recommend cases for:

- missing smoke path
- missing happy path
- missing required-field validation
- missing invalid-format validation
- missing boundary test
- missing permission denial
- missing duplicate prevention
- missing state transition
- missing API failure handling
- missing DB persistence verification
- missing pagination/search/filter scenario
- missing regression scenario from linked module
- missing fixed-defect regression

New cases must follow all field standards in this rule.

---

# Qase Update Rules

When Qase MCP is available, update each changed case using one update call per case.

Do not make separate calls per field.

Update payload must include all corrected fields.

Required Qase values:

```text
type: 3
layer: 1
is_flaky: 0
automation: 1
status: 0
behavior: 2 or 3
severity: per matrix
priority: per matrix
```

Every step object must include:

```text
action
expected_result
data
```

Use empty string for data only when no input is required.

Do not expose enum numbers in the user-facing summary. Use labels instead.

---

# Review Decision Algorithm

For each test case:

1. Read the title, description, preconditions, steps, severity, priority, type, layer, behavior, status, automation, and flaky fields.
2. Identify the tested requirement or mark it as untraced.
3. Verify the test's behavior classification.
4. Verify severity and priority using the matrix.
5. Verify type, layer, status, automation, and flaky values.
6. Verify the description explains purpose and value.
7. Verify preconditions are role/state/start-point based and contain no real data.
8. Verify every step has an atomic action, observable expected result, and appropriate test data.
9. Verify test data is safe, concrete, and aligned with positive or negative behavior.
10. Verify grammar, UI labels, and terminology.
11. Decide:
    - no change
    - update existing case
    - split into multiple cases
    - merge duplicate case
    - mark obsolete
    - create missing case
12. Record the reason for every material change.

